      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The Washington Water Power\nCo. has served notice on the city\nthat d. Boyington, the contractor\nbuilding the North Howard street\nbridge. has broken down the dam\nwhich holds the water for the Cen\ntennial mill. The company advises\nthat the city see to 1t that the dam\nis repaired at once before the high\nwater sets in. otherwise the city\nmay be held liable for damages to\nthe mill.\n\n\nAnother complaint was made that\nthe contractor intends to leave the\ncOfferdam In the stream and to this\nobstruction the company also OBJ\n1ects and asks that II be removed\nbefore the high water interferes\nWith the work."
    }
